#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/initial_messages.lua:15
msgid "The Story Begins"
msgstr "Tha an sgeulachd air tòiseachadh"

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/initial_messages.lua:16
msgid "Thron sighs..."
msgstr "Tha Thron ag osnachadh..."

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/initial_messages.lua:17
msgid ""
"It’s been months, and we are still hiding where the forests are old and dark."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/initial_messages.lua:18
msgid ""
"My warriors hunt at day and lie awake at night – listening to the sounds of "
"the cruel slaughter echoing from afar amongst the ancient trees."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/initial_messages.lua:23
msgid ""
"We can see the raging flames that swallow Al’thunran from here, miles away."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/initial_messages.lua:24
msgid ""
"The red lights flash in the darkness and dance to the rhythm of the war "
"drums that haunt me even in my nightmares."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/initial_messages.lua:28
msgid ""
"My father’s bones rest peacefully in the ground on which he once ended the "
"senseless spilling of blood that had arisen amongst us. It pains me that his "
"peace only endured for one generation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/initial_messages.lua:29
msgid ""
"Boldreth, my loyal companion and friend is a source of peace and comfort to "
"me in these dark times. He keeps my spirits high and those of my warriors "
"awake, preventing greed or despair from destroying the bonds between us as "
"well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/initial_messages.lua:33
msgid ""
"As father told me, there are times to fight and times to lie and wait, "
"trying not to fall asleep or die before the right time comes. And so I do... "
"wait."
msgstr ""
"Mar a dh'innis m' athair dhomh, bidh àm cogaidh ann 's àm gus dol am falach "
"'s a' feitheamh, a' feuchainn nach tig cadal no bàs ort mus tig an t-àm "
"dhut. 'S e seo na nì mi... feitheamh."

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/khantrukhs_talking.lua:23
msgid "Somebody Comes up to You"
msgstr "Tha cuideigin a' teannadh a-nall"

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/khantrukhs_talking.lua:24
#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/khantrukhs_talking.lua:31
#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/khantrukhs_talking.lua:38
#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/khantrukhs_talking.lua:39
#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/khantrukhs_talking.lua:47
#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/khantrukhs_talking.lua:54
msgid "The Advisor"
msgstr "An comhairleach"

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/khantrukhs_talking.lua:60
msgid "Mission Complete"
msgstr "Tha am misean coileanta"

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:17
#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:19
#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:31
#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:33
msgid "Build a lumberjack’s hut"
msgstr "Tog bothan coillteir"

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:20
#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:34
msgid ""
"Press SPACE to see where you can build. The red house symbols show you where "
"a small building – like a lumberjack’s hut – may be built."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:21
#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:35
msgid ""
"Build a lumberjack’s hut at the red house symbol just right of your "
"headquarters by clicking on it and selecting a lumberjack’s hut."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:22
#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:44
msgid ""
"Build a road between your headquarters and the construction site of the "
"lumberjack’s hut."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:23
#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:45
msgid ""
"When you place the lumberjack’s hut, a flag is created for it. You need to "
"connect it to another flag by building a road between them. If you click on "
"a flag and select to build a road, little symbols will appear around it to "
"show you in which directions you can build it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:24
#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:46
msgid ""
"The colors of these symbols indicate how steep this part of the road will "
"be. Green is for flat, yellow means steep and red stands for very steep. The "
"steeper the road is, the harder it will be for your people to walk on it "
"(and your wares will be transported more slowly)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:41
msgid "Build a road to the lumberjack’s hut"
msgstr "Tog rathad dhan bhothan coillteir"

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:43
msgid "Road to the lumberjack’ hut"
msgstr "Rathad dhan bhothan coillteir"

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:47
msgid ""
"You can click on any of the symbols to build the first part of the road "
"there. New symbols will appear to show you where the next part of the road "
"can go, and so on. However, you can also click farther away from the flag to "
"build several steps at once. Click on the flag at the headquarters to finish "
"the road."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:53
#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:55
#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:64
#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:66
#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:74
#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:76
msgid "Build a second lumberjack’s hut"
msgstr "Tog bothan coillteir eile"

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:56
#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:67
msgid ""
"Place a flag in the middle of the road. There is a flag symbol in the middle "
"of the road you just built. You create a flag there by clicking on the "
"symbol and then choosing the flag button in the menu that opens up. This "
"will divide the road the wood is transported into two parts with one carrier "
"each."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:57
#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:77
msgid ""
"Place a lumberjack’s hut just south of the flag you just placed on the road. "
"Connect the flag you just raised with the flag of the new lumberjack’s hut "
"construction site afterwards. Note that instead of building a road step by "
"step, you may also click directly at its destination to build the entire "
"road at once."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:58
#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:68
msgid ""
"When many wares are being transported between two points, additional flags "
"in between make them arrive at their destination faster, thus improving your "
"infrastructure."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:83
#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:85
msgid "Build a ranger’s hut"
msgstr "Tog bothan maoir-choille"

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:86
msgid "Build a ranger’s hut to the east of the first lumberjack’s hut."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:92
#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:94
msgid "Build two quarries"
msgstr "Tog dà choireall"

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:95
msgid "Build two quarries south-west of your headquarters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:103
msgid "An old man says..."
msgstr "Tha bodach a' bruidhinn riut..."

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:104
msgid ""
"Hail, chieftain. I am Khantrukh and have seen many winters pass. Please "
"allow me to aid you with my counsel through these darkened days."
msgstr ""
"Fàilte, a cheannaird. 'S mise Khantrukh is chunnaic mi iomadh geamhradh a' "
"dol seachad. Gum faodainn ur cuideachadh le comhairle rè nan làithean dorcha "
"seo."

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:106
msgid "Khantrukh continues..."
msgstr "Tha Khantrukh a' leantainn air adhart..."

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:107
msgid ""
"None but the gods know how long we have to remain hidden here. The warriors "
"hope we may march back gloriously any day now, but I strongly doubt that "
"will happen soon. And the days are already getting shorter and colder..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:108
msgid ""
"We should prepare, in case we have to face the winter in these harsh lands. "
"I believe to the east of our campsite are a few places where we could raise "
"a lumberjack’s hut."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:111
msgid "The elder remarks..."
msgstr "Tha an seanair a' beachdachadh..."

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:112
msgid ""
"Obviously, it would be too exhausting for our people to walk all the way to "
"the lumberjack’s hut through the wilderness. We will have to build a road "
"between our hall and the lumberjack’s hut. It’s not a hard guess that the "
"men would appreciate a way as short and plain as possible – the wood will "
"surely be heavy enough, nevertheless."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:115
msgid "Khantrukh remembers..."
msgstr "Tha cuimhne air Khantrukh..."

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:116
msgid "There is an old saying:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:117
msgid "‘A burden divided is easier to endure.’"
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:118
msgid ""
"A crossroads on the road between our headquarters and the lumberjack’s hut "
"would ease the work of our carriers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:121
msgid "The old man looks to the sky..."
msgstr "Tha am bodach a' coimhead dha na speuran..."

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:122
msgid ""
"The northern winds tell us that the coming winter will be a long and cruel "
"one. One lumberjack’s hut will not be enough to serve the needs of our "
"people. More trees await our axes just south of our new crossroads – let us "
"raise a second lumberjack’s hut there!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:125
msgid "Khantrukh nods..."
msgstr "Tha Khantrukh ag aontachadh..."

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:126
msgid ""
"Of course, if we intended to build a bigger settlement, many more "
"lumberjack’s huts would be advisable, but this should suffice for now."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:127
msgid ""
"But never forget – these forests are our heritage, entrusted upon us by our "
"ancestors. We must always respect and care for them. What we take, we must "
"give back again."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:128
msgid ""
"So, in order to replace the trees we chop down, we should build a ranger’s "
"hut, preferably close to the lumberjack’s hut."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:131
msgid "The elder speaks..."
msgstr "Tha an seanair ag ràdh..."

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:132
msgid ""
"I am well aware, chieftain, that neither you nor your warriors have the "
"desire to stay in this forsaken place for long. But even so, our war to "
"reconquer our home might take a long time and it would seem wise to make "
"preparations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:133
msgid ""
"I would advise that we obtain stones for the future – who knows what "
"fortifications we might be forced to build very soon. And – like a gift of "
"destiny – there are indeed great rocks just nearby..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:136
msgid ""
"Very well done, chieftain. We now have all we need to face the winter and "
"may prepare ourselves for the battles ahead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:137
msgid "Victory"
msgstr "Buaidh"

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:138
msgid ""
"You may continue to play this map if you wish. Otherwise, move on to the "
"next mission."
msgstr ""
"Faodaidh tu leantainn air adhart a' cluiche a' mhapa seo ma thogras tu no "
"gluasad air adhart dhan ath-mhisean."

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:145
msgid "In the Night"
msgstr "Air an oidhche"

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:146
#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:154
msgid "Thron says..."
msgstr "Tha Thron a' bruidhinn..."

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:147
msgid ""
"During another sleepless night, I went up to the hill and gazed towards the "
"north. The fires are still burning, satisfying their hunger upon my father’s "
"legacy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:148
msgid ""
"They are a constant reminder of why we have to hide here... and why we must "
"return in the end!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:153
msgid "At the Tomb"
msgstr "Aig an uaigh"

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:155
msgid ""
"Once again, I went up to my father’s tomb, in a sacred grove at the foot of "
"the great spire of Kal’mavrath. I just stood there and felt neither the "
"hours pass nor the cold rain pouring down from the darkened sky..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:156
msgid ""
"Somehow, it felt like a farewell. For the first time, I wondered what the "
"future might hold for me..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:161
msgid "The Other Day"
msgstr "An latha eile"

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:162
msgid "Thron says thoughtfully..."
msgstr "Tha Thron a' cnuasadh..."

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:163
msgid ""
"Some time ago, Boldreth came to me. His advice was to move to a place closer "
"to home – to strike at the first sign of my brothers’ forces wavering."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:164
msgid ""
"But when I look over the forests I can still see black smoke rising to the "
"sky. I know – it is too early yet, and what he hopes for will not happen any "
"time soon. He might still be right, but I fear the bloodshed that returning "
"too fast would cause both on our and the other side..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:168
msgid "The Oath"
msgstr "A' bhòid"

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:169
msgid "Thron looks furious..."
msgstr "Tha an ainmein air Thron..."

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:170
msgid ""
"Today, my warriors picked up an old man, wandering sick and wounded through "
"the dark forest. We listened in horror as he told us of the atrocities "
"taking place in Al’thunran."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/t01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:171
msgid "I hereby renew my oath – I will stop this madness at any cost!"
msgstr ""

